history.content: Three technical courses, including 61C and Physics, sounds like a lot to me. It is possible, but you will want to consider other things you might have going on during that semester (ie teaching, research, family obligations, clubs, personal interest, etc) to see if you really have time to commit to 3 techs. I will let students weigh in to see if anyone has taken this exact schedule previously.

How difficult does this schedule sound? I could potentially push the humanities to a later semester and/or push CS61C off to summer, but if 61C and 170 seems reasonable I would prefer that.

Thanks!
history.subject: CS61C + CS170 + Physics 7B + Humanities
